Trevor Noah attends the 62nd Annual GRAMMY Awards at STAPLES Center on January 26, 2020 in Los Angeles, California. JOHANNESBURG - South African comedian Trevor Noah has confirmed that he will partner with Rafael Nadal against Roger Federer and Microsoft billionaire Bill Gates for a tennis match in Cape Town in February. According to the ATP Tour website, the match forms part of Federer’s 'Match for Africa' series which aims to raise funds that will benefit the children in the region. READ: Trevor Noah scores Critics Choice award nomination Noah sent a friendly warning to his opponents on Wednesday, reminding them that local fans will probably be on his side. "Hey@RogerFederer, you &@billgates want to play doubles against me & @RafaelNadal!? Okay. We accept your challenge, but be prepared for the crowd in SA to be on our side! See you Feb 7 in Cape Town! Masihambe!," said Noah. Nadal and Federer will clash for the first time in Africa at the Cape Town Stadium on Friday, February 7 at 20:00.